  "text": "Specific questions were: \"What time do you usually go to bed on weekends?\" and \"What time do you usually wake up on weekends?\" Midsleep on weekends was calculated as follows: bedtime + the half of sleep length on weekends. Middle point of time in bed (the midpoint between bedtime and rising time), which is a proxy for MSF (the midpoint between sleep onset and waking) was used [CITATION_1] . Higher scores in MSF indicate a delay of sleep-wake rhythm.",
